@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Personal Information Collection: Clearly explain what personal information you collect from customers, including their name, address, email, phone number, payment information, and any other data they provide during the purchasing process." +
    "\r\n\r\nUse of Personal Information: Explain how the personal information you collect is used, such as to fulfill orders, process payments, and provide customer support." +
    "\r\n\r\nSharing of Personal Information: Clearly state whether you share customer data with third parties, and if so, for what purposes." +
    "\r\n\r\nCookies and Tracking: Explain how you use cookies and tracking technologies on your website, and how you collect and use data about user behavior to improve the customer experience." +
    "\r\n\r\nData Security: Explain how you protect customer data, such as through encryption, firewalls, and other security measures." +
    "\r\n\r\nAccess to Personal Information: Explain how customers can access and modify their personal information, and how they can request that their data be deleted." +
    "\r\n\r\nCompliance: Explain how you comply with relevant laws and regulations, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) in the European Union or the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) in the United States." +
    "\r\n\r\nContact Information: Provide a contact email or phone number where customers can reach you with questions or concerns about their privacy.\r\n\r\n"]</h1>

<p>Use this page to detail your site's privacy policy.</p>
